Chunk = {"chunk":[{"ty":"is","ibi":1,"s":"04/02/2025\nbeta meassures the correlation.\nSpot/vol beta means how much the spot and the volatility, atm vol, fix strike vol moves together.\nwhen it is negative, they move opposite.\nwhen it is positive, they move together.\nof course, it has a spectrum, not black\u0026white.\nthe \"normal\"  version is the negative (short) spot/vol beta, when spot up/vol down.\nwhy? bcs it his case, investors are long stock, and use hedges to hedge the downside by buying OTM puts and selling OTM calls, buying the skew. (bcs skew is 25d put minus 25d call)\nby doing this, they put market makers (who take the opposite of the trade: long OTM calls, short OTM puts, selling the skew) into long vanna: so as spot moves up, they become longer vega that they hedge by selling vol. \nThis reflexively dumps volatility down if market moves up.\nBut if market moves down, MMs become shorter vega, means they have to buy vol. reflexively increasing volatility.\nand not just that... gamma: they are longer upside gamma, and shorter downside gamma (positive speed). \nSo, volatility compresses to the upside (as more trading against the price actions), and expands to the downside, resulting: NEGATIVE SPOT/VOL BETA.\nbut if the opposite happens, mania on the options market, and right-tail hedging: investors buying OTM calls and selling OTM puts, selling the skew. \nthis puts market makers into long skew, and short vanna, means: as spot moves up, they become shorter vega, so they need to buy vega. \nAlso shorter upside gamma, and longer downside gamma (negative speed)\nSo vol expands if market moves up, createing right-tail risk, low liquidity to the upside due to this one-sided crowded trade.\nAnd compresses to the downside, as there where liquidity stands. \nThis results POSITIVE SPOT/VOL BETA\nif the bid effects the tails as well, tail OTM puts (that are synthetic VIX calls), bidding also vol of vol, you will see positive spot/vix beta. thats when blow-off top happens.\nwhat net zero speed is\nwhere MMs shift from short skew positioning to long skew.\ni just explained the spot/vol beta above, read that. but i will write about these concepts more deeply, from the very basics to the advanced things. \nabove zero speed, MMs are longer skew: longer spot/vol beta, shorter upside gamma/longer downside gamma \nbelow zero speed, MMs are shorter skew: shorter spot/vol beta, longer upside gamma/shorter downside gamma. \nso thats kind of a balance, where MMs gamma exposure shifts. above they have more gamma to the downside than to the upside, and vice versa\nHow can we tell which of the three greeks- speed, vanna, charm- has the greatest impact to the spot price movement? Let\u0027s say we are in the middle of a \"positive speed \u0026 positive vanna \u0026 negative charm\" area, and the spot price is going upwards. Here is my understanding: 1. Positive speed has a downward effect because spot up→gamma up→MMs buy less or sell more delta 2. Positive vanna has an upward effect because spot up→vol down→delta down→MMs buy delta 3. Negative charm has an upward effect because time passes→delta down→MMs buy delta\nthink this way: supportive doesn\u0027t necessary means \"pushing up\". from this perspective short speed is more \"supportive\" with its fat right-tail risk. but supportive means stabilizing, more liqudiity, vol can compress. so maybe the price is pinned, but stabile ins a huge positive gamma territory.\nvanna has a complex effect, it is usually have a longer-time frame effect, but vanna is not easy, that will get an individual long post to explain. charm has very little effect usually... it comes into play at the end of the day. and also it is increased if vol is high, especially around the 25 delta strikes. \nmost of the times it is gamma. gamma has an inverse relationship with volatility, and it must be hedged instantly\n\nyou mentioned that vol of vol decreasing meaning that traders are rolling their vix positions into March Opex? How do you get this relationship? When vol of vol decreases automatically people roll why can’t they decrease their puts therefore decreasing the vol\n"},{"ty":"as","st":"document","si":0,"ei":0,"sm":{"ds_pw":595.3,"ds_mt":70.85,"ds_lhs":1,"ds_mr":56.7,"ds_mb":56.7,"ds_rtd":"mso-rtd.0","ds_ulhfl":false,"ds_ml":56.7,"ds_mh":35.4,"ds_ph":841.9,"ds_mf":35.4}},{"ty":"ae","et":"list","id":"kix.list.1","epm":{"le_nb":{"nl_4":{"b_gf":"%4","b_ts":{"ts_un":false,"ts_un_i":true,"ts_sc":false,"ts_it_i":true,"ts_fgc2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0},"ts_st_i":true,"ts_bgc2":{"hclr_color":null,"clr_type":0},"ts_fs_i":true,"ts_ff_i":false,"ts_bgc2_i":true,"ts_it":false,"ts_va":"nor","ts_bd_i":true,"ts_va_i":true,"ts_fs":11.0,"ts_ff":"Courier New","ts_st":false,"ts_bd":false,"ts_fgc2_i":true,"ts_sc_i":true,"ts_tw":400},"b_ifl":162.0,"b_gs":"o","b_a":0,"b_sn":1,"b_gt":9,"b_il":180.0},"nl_3":{"b_gf":"%3","b_ts":{"ts_un":false,"ts_un_i":true,"ts_sc":false,"ts_it_i":true,"ts_fgc2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0},"ts_st_i":true,"ts_bgc2":{"hclr_color":null,"clr_type":0},"ts_fs_i":true,"ts_ff_i":false,"ts_bgc2_i":true,"ts_it":false,"ts_va":"nor","ts_bd_i":true,"ts_va_i":true,"ts_fs":11.0,"ts_ff":"Noto Sans Symbols","ts_st":false,"ts_bd":false,"ts_fgc2_i":true,"ts_sc_i":true,"ts_tw":400},"b_ifl":126.0,"b_gs":"●","b_a":0,"b_sn":1,"b_gt":9,"b_il":144.0},"nl_2":{"b_gf":"%2","b_ts":{"ts_un":false,"ts_un_i":true,"ts_sc":false,"ts_it_i":true,"ts_fgc2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0},"ts_st_i":true,"ts_bgc2":{"hclr_color":null,"clr_type":0},"ts_fs_i":true,"ts_ff_i":false,"ts_bgc2_i":true,"ts_it":false,"ts_va":"nor","ts_bd_i":true,"ts_va_i":true,"ts_fs":11.0,"ts_ff":"Noto Sans Symbols","ts_st":false,"ts_bd":false,"ts_fgc2_i":true,"ts_sc_i":true,"ts_tw":400},"b_ifl":90.0,"b_gs":"▪","b_a":0,"b_sn":1,"b_gt":9,"b_il":108.0},"nl_1":{"b_gf":"%1","b_ts":{"ts_un":false,"ts_un_i":true,"ts_sc":false,"ts_it_i":true,"ts_fgc2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0},"ts_st_i":true,"