 so VIX futs have no linearity in the underlying index. so the longer-term the contract is the lower its delta is, even \u003c50, but never 1. this makes vol market exciting\nMarket is influenced by the derivative market\nit is all about constant betting. Plp are betting on outcomes with different probabilities on different timeframes, and this creates a feedback loop through the vol market first. i won\u0027t go into it now. \njust think about it: there is a company, and there is a stock of a company. the company has a productivity, performance rate, ... quality in overall, a value, and the stock is meant to \u0027express\u0027/\u0027manifest\u0027 that value but white collars came and they said: lets create derivates on that, like futures to buy the stock at a certain spot at a certain time and bcs the future contract has a different liquidity profile, different supply/demand profile, its pricing can deviate from the actual value of the stock\nso what do I mean? futures are tradeable products. you don\u0027t necessary buy a fut contract bcs you want to buy the stock. you buy it bcs you speculates (like me this morning) and the supply/demand dynamics effect its price but it reflexively creates liquidity on the underlying stock bcs somebody somewhere will buy or sell that stock and there are options another layer of betting\nthe big diff is that here you can exercise it whenever you want (ok, depends on if it is American or European style, but this is not my point now) but! and this is the main thing here options are not one-delta assets this is crucial.\nwhat is delta? it is a rate that shows you how a certain asset follows another one. like a stock is 1 delta, bcs it goes 1:1 with itself. A future is also usually 1 delta, as its value moves together with the underlying (except for VIX futs, bcs of the fluctuating spot/vol correlation) but an option can be 0 to 1 delta multiplied by 100 bcs one contract covers 100 options. So if you buy an 50 delta option, its like buying 50 shares of stocks, if you by a 23 delta option, its like having 23 shares of stocks notionally and this is the true meaning of DEX tho, giving you the notional size of the trade.\nBut when you buy it, somebody must sell it. and the one who sold you will notionally short sell 50 shares of stocks, so he will have a risk exposure he must hedge it by purchasing 50 shares or futs and so, the key point here is that you already created a situation, when somebody must trade with the underlying asset due to hedging, not bcs of the value of the company and the wild thing is the options on futures... betting on the bet etc. just like in the Big Short movie in the Vegas scene.\nNow bet has a time maturity this is the second dimension of it. simple, right? you bet on that SPX will reach lets say 6050 by friday through long 6050 call. but on friday then, the bet will be closed, and you either won or lost the third one is the standard deviation of the returns, aka volatility.\n"},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":8331,"ei":8331,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_bb":{"brdr_c2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0},"brdr_s":1.0,"brdr_w":0.75,"brdr_ls":0},"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":true,"ps_bl_i":true,"ps_sd_i":true,"ps_sb_i":true,"ps_sa_i":true,"ps_lslm_i":true,"ps_br_i":true,"ps_bbtw_i":true,"ps_kwn_i":true,"ps_bt_i":true,"ps_ifl_i":true,"ps_bb_i":false,"ps_pbb_i":true}},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":8465,"ei":8465,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_bb":{"brdr_c2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0},"brdr_s":1.0,"brdr_w":0.75,"brdr_ls":0},"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":true,"ps_bl_i":true,"ps_sd_i":true,"ps_sb_i":true,"ps_sa_i":true,"ps_lslm_i":true,"ps_br_i":true,"ps_bbtw_i":true,"ps_kwn_i":true,"ps_bt_i":true,"ps_ifl_i":true,"ps_bb_i":false,"ps_pbb_i":true}},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":8647,"ei":8647,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_bb":{"brdr_c2":{"hclr